Reasoning: The paper deals with computer vision tasks such as fruit detection, segmentation, and counting in orchard environments. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses baseline performance analysis and yield estimation, which suggests that it may belong to sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the dataset may also be relevant to robotics applications, which could place it in the cs.RO (Robotics) sub-category.
